'''Kinoe''' (甲) is the first of the {{ill|Heavenly Stems|lt=Ten Heavenly Stems|8=en|ja|十干|en|qq=|12=draft}}.<ref>[https://skdesu.com/en/meaning/%E7%94%B2-kinoe/ 甲 | kinoe - Meaning in Japanese]</ref><ref>[https://www.tanoshiijapanese.com/dictionary/entry_details.cfm?entry_id=55812 <nowiki>Entry Details for 甲 [kou] - Tanoshii Japanese</nowiki>]</ref>

According to the {{ill|Yin-Yang and Five Elements theory|ja|陰陽五行説|1=Yin-Yang and Wuxing Theory|qq=|12=draft}}, it is associated with the yang aspect of the {{ill|Wood (wuxing)|lt=wood element|ja|木|qq=|12=draft}}, and in Japan, it is referred to as "{{ill|Kinoe (甲)|kinoe|ja|きのえ|qq=|12=draft}}" (elder wood).

== Overview ==
* The origin of the character "甲" has been the subject of various proposals, but no definitive theory has been established.<ref>{{Citation| author=于省吾| year=1996| title=甲骨文字誁林| location=Beijing| publisher=中華書局| isbn=7-101-01430-5| pages=3582–6|qq=}}</ref> Its use as a term to denote the first of the Ten Heavenly Stems is due to {{ill|phonetic loan|ja|仮借|qq=|12=draft}}.
* When used for Ranking, "Kō" signifies the first position. Additionally, it is used in classification names such as "{{ill|Kōrui|ja|甲類|qq=|12=draft}}" and "{{ill|Kōshu|ja|甲種|qq=|12=draft}}," though these do not necessarily indicate superiority in Rank.
* In the {{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|西暦|1=Common Era|2=ja|3=西暦|4=zh|5=公元|6=es|7=Era común|8=nl|9=Gangbare jaartelling|10=simple|11=Common Era|qq=|12=draft}}, years ending with the digit 4 are considered "Kō" years. The alternative name for the year is "{{ill|Afu|ja|閼逢|qq=|12=draft}}" (also written as "{{ill|Appō|ja|閼蓬|qq=|12=draft}}" or "{{ill|Enpō|ja|焉逢|qq=|12=draft}}").<ref>{{Cite web |title=Dictionary Entry [閼逢: アツホウ] |url=https://dict.revised.moe.edu.tw/dictView.jsp?ID=147004&la=0&powerMode=0 |website=Ministry of Education Revised Chinese Dictionary 2021 |access-date=2024-03-08 |language=zh-Hant-TW|qq=}}</ref>
* In {{ill|Chinese chemical nomenclature|ja|化合物命名法|qq=|12=draft}}, it is used to denote compounds and {{ill|functional groups|ja|官能基|qq=|12=draft}} containing one carbon atom, such as {{ill|methane|ja|メタン|qq=|12=draft}} and {{ill|methyl group|ja|メチル基|qq=|12=draft}}.
* Its opposite counterpart is {{ill|Ki (己)|ja|己|1=Tsuchinoto (己)|qq=|12=draft}} (tsuchinoto).
* The {{ill|lucky direction|ja|恵方|3=歳徳神|1=Toshitoku-shin|lt=Lucky direction|qq=|12=draft}} associated with Kō is slightly east of northeast (75 degrees).


